the_theatre_of_living_arts.note: There is limited metered street parking near the venue. Commercial lots are available on 5th and Bainbridge Streets, but they accept cash only. The venue has partnered with ParkWhiz for additional parking options.

the_van_buren.note: There is no on-site parking at The Van Buren. They have partnered with ParkWhiz for parking options nearby. Limited metered street parking and nearby paid lots are available, but fill up quickly.

the_wiltern.note: The Wiltern offers premium underground parking and upgrades for select shows. The most convenient parking option is the Ralphs parking structure adjacent to the venue, accessible from Oxford Street through the north entrance.

thunder_ridge_nature_arena.note: General admission parking is free with a valid concert ticket, while Diamond and Premium parking are available for purchase. ADA parking is also free with a valid ticket. Tailgating is allowed with restrictions, and RV parking is available without hookups.
thunder_ridge_nature_arena.rideshare: Rideshare is labeled 'Rideshare & Guest Pick up/Drop off' with tram services offered before and after an event.

tmobile_center.note: The T-Mobile Center offers convenient on-site parking in the Magenta Lot, available for advance purchase on a first-come, first-served basis. Additional parking is available at the Red Lot Parking Garage and the Yellow Lot Parking Garage. Parking links for concerts can be found on individual event pages.
tmobile_center.rideshare: Oak Street is open for passenger drop-off, including taxi or ride-share drop-off. It is also the place for ADA drop-off.

tmobile_park.note: Parking options include the T-Mobile Park Garage, Stadium Exhibition Center Garage, Union Station Garage, and the North Lot. Expect heavy traffic congestion for about 45 minutes post-game, especially on First Avenue at Royal Brougham Way.

talking_stick_resort_amphitheatre.note: Parking lots open 30 minutes before gate time. Premier Parking and Easy Out Parking are available for easier entry and exit. Arrive early to secure your spot.
talking_stick_resort_amphitheatre.rideshare: For rideshares, head to Palm Lane on the southwest side of the venue.

tottenham_hotspur_stadium.note: There is no public parking available at or around Tottenham Hotspur Stadium. Visitors are advised not to drive to events due to parking restrictions and the operation of tow trucks. Cycling is encouraged with ample cycle parking available.

toyota_center.note: Toyota Center offers a dedicated 2,500-space parking garage called the Toyota Tundra Garage, which is cashless and has a private sky bridge for premium guests. Garage parking is not available for non-passholders on Houston Rockets game days. Surface parking lots and street parking are also available nearby.

truist_park.note: Parking options include discounted offsite parking at Skyview Mall and various lots around Citi Field. Prices range from $10-20 at Skyview Mall and $40-120 at Citi Field depending on the event and vehicle type. Cashless payments are required.

ubc_doug_mitchell_thunderbird_sports_cen.note: Parking is available at Thunderbird Parkade, the closest to the venue, and Health Sciences Parkade, which offers quicker exit times. Event rates may vary, and payment can be made via the HonkMobile app on the day of the event.
ubc_doug_mitchell_thunderbird_sports_cen.venueName: UBC – Doug Mitchell Thunderbird Sports Centre

ubs_arena.note: Parking is available for purchase prior to events via ParkWhiz and Ticketmaster, with prices increasing by $5-$10 at the arena. General paid parking is available at Emerald Parking, with additional lots accessible via the Cross Island Parkway.

uc_berkeley_greek_theatre.note: Parking is very limited around the Greek Theatre, and it's recommended to use public transportation, biking, or carpooling. UC Berkeley lots near the venue open at 5:00pm, accept credit cards only, and have limited spots. Disabled parking is available at Upper Hearst parking garage.

us_bank_stadium.note: There are over 20,000 parking spaces available within a 20-minute walk of U.S. Bank Stadium. Parking lots typically open six hours before events and close two hours after. Accessible parking is available in all lots and ramps.

unipol_arena.note: Unipol Arena offers parking for 5000 cars and has reserved spaces for disabled people. Accredited disabled users can access free parking via a separate entrance.

unipol_forum.note: Unipol Forum offers ample parking near the venue, with Park B being a notable option. Electric car charging is available at a hub in front of the Repower Theatre. Parking fees during events start from €10.

unity_arena.note: No specific parking options, pricing, or tips are mentioned in the provided content.

usher_hall.note: No specific parking options, pricing, or tips are mentioned on the page.

utah_first_credit_union_amphitheatre.note: General admission parking is included with your ticket. Upgraded options such as Premier Parking, Ultra Premier Parking, and Reserved Parking are available, with Reserved Parking ensuring a quick exit after the event. All parking lots are conveniently located on the east side of the venue.
utah_first_credit_union_amphitheatre.rideshare: Rideshare drop off and pick up is available at 5150 Upper Ridge Rd., West Valley City, UT 84118.

utilita_arena_birmingham.note: Utilita Arena Birmingham offers convenient parking options with North, South, and West car parks. Pre-booking is recommended to secure a spot, especially for the West car park, which is reserved for pre-booked and Premium customers. Accessible parking is available in designated areas.

utilita_arena_newcastle.note: There are over 600 official car park spaces available on site with CCTV and security patrols. When full, the NCP Car Park next to the Arena is recommended. Pre-booking is not available and parking for cars with wheelchair patrons is on a first-come, first-served basis.
utilita_arena_newcastle.rideshare: Dropping off can be made along Railway Street. Collecting people is advised to be done away from the Arena due to heavy traffic.

utilita_arena_sheffield.note: On-site parking at Utilita Arena Sheffield often sells out in advance, so it's recommended to purchase parking tickets online beforehand for guaranteed reserved parking. Parking is for one admission only, and re-entry is not allowed.

uw_panther_arena.note: The Baird Center Garage offers convenient indoor parking with easy access to events at UW-Milwaukee Panther Arena and nearby venues. Additional parking options are available throughout downtown Milwaukee, including street spots and nearby garages.

van_andel_arena.note: Parking facilities near Van Andel Arena are managed by the City of Grand Rapids. Metered parking is available on surrounding streets, and accessible parking is available in city-owned ramps and lots on a first-come, first-served basis.

veterans_memorial_coliseum.note: The Rose Quarter offers over 2500 parking spaces across four garages and two lots, with prices ranging from $10 to $40 depending on the event. Pre-paid parking is available for most events, and motorcycle parking costs the same as regular vehicles.

veterans_united_home_loans_amphitheater.note: General admission parking is included with your ticket. For easier entry and exit, consider upgrading to Premier Parking or VIP Parking.

videotron_centre.note: Parking is accessible via Soumande St. and Avenue du Colisée. Customers have free access to the P2B parking lot via Soumande St., except on event days when parking fees apply.

viejas_arena.note: Event parking is available at Parking Structures 3 and 6/6B for $40 per vehicle, payable via credit/debit cards or mobile payment options. Parking areas open 90 minutes before event doors open, and overnight parking and tailgating are prohibited.

villa_erba.note: No specific parking options or pricing information available on the website. Visitors may need to inquire directly with the venue for parking details.

wamu_theater.note: Paid parking is available at the Lumen Field Event Center Garage, which opens at 6 a.m. on event days and closes 2 hours after the event. Pre-purchase parking options are available for most events. Electric vehicle charging is available, but parking is not guaranteed without pre-purchase.

walmart_amp.note: Parking is available on-site at Walmart AMP with options for both general and premium parking. Prices may vary based on the event and parking location. It's recommended to arrive early to secure a spot and avoid congestion.

wells_fargo_arena.note: Parking options around Wells Fargo Arena include several nearby lots and garages. Prices may vary depending on the event, and it's advisable to arrive early to secure a spot. Street parking may also be available but can be limited during major events.

wells_fargo_center.note: Parking at Xfinity Mobile Arena can be reserved in advance through SpotHero for up to 50% off drive-up rates. Accessible parking is available near entrances, and daily subway parking is offered in Lot A on weekdays.

wembley_stadium.note: Wembley Stadium is primarily a public transport destination with easy access via three railway stations. Visitors driving to the stadium should be aware of the Ultra Low Emission Zone (ULEZ) charges applicable to non-compliant vehicles.

winstar_lucas_oil_live.note: Valet parking is available 24/7 for hotel guests at the Pool Tower entrance. Pricing varies based on membership status: Elite Club Passport Members park for free, Premier Members pay $5, Base Members pay $15, and non-carded patrons pay $20.

wrigley_field.note: The page provides information about parking at Citi Field, not Wrigley Field. It mentions discounted offsite parking at Skyview Mall and various parking lots with prices ranging from $10-20 for offsite parking and $40-60 for regular season and special events. Payment is cashless, and there are options for oversized vehicles.

xl_center.note: Parking is available around the PeoplesBank Arena and throughout Downtown Hartford, with 45 lots and garages. Prices vary and are managed by third-party companies. Metered street parking is free from 6:00 pm to 8:00 am and all day on weekends.

xcel_energy_center.note: Parking is available at RiverCentre and Kellogg Parking Ramps, both connected to the arena. Event day parking is first come, first served, and ParkWhiz reservations are not available for these ramps.
xcel_energy_center.rideshare: Gate 4 on 5th Street is the official pick-up and drop-off location for ride share services.

yankee_stadium.note: Parking is available at Citi Field with regular season car rates at $40 and postseason rates at $60. The parking lots open one hour before stadium gates, and payment is cashless, accepting credit/debit cards and mobile payments.

coachella_valley_music_and_arts_festival.venueName: Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival

ultra_music_festival.note: No specific parking options, pricing, or tips are mentioned for the Ultra Music Festival.

edc_las_vegas.note: Premier Parking is available for purchase and offers easier access, while General Parking is free. ADA Parking is also available. All parking lots open at 3pm on Friday and 5pm on Saturday and Sunday.
edc_las_vegas.rideshare: All rideshare, taxi, and general drop-offs and pickups must occur at the designated Guest Drop-Off and Pickup location (Mid-Brown Lot).

electric_forest.note: No specific parking options, pricing, or tips are mentioned on the provided page. Attendees are encouraged to check the official website for updates.

bonnaroo_music_arts_festival.note: Parking is available onsite for festival attendees. It is recommended to arrive early to secure a spot as parking can fill up quickly. Be prepared for potential long walks from parking areas to the festival entrance.

governors_ball.note: There is no event parking available, so festival organizers urge all concertgoers to take public transit. Bicycle parking is available at the front entrance, but riders must bring their own locks.
governors_ball.rideshare: There is a designated pick-up and drop-off area on Shea Road.

outside_lands.note: Parking information is not provided on the official website. Attendees are encouraged to use public transportation or rideshare services due to limited parking availability in the area.

lollapalooza.note: Parking options around Lollapalooza in Chicago may include nearby public parking lots and garages. Prices can vary, and it is advisable to arrive early to secure a spot. Consider using public transportation or rideshare services to avoid parking hassles.

rolling_loud_miami.note: Parking at the stadium is sold out, but Park & Ride passes are still available. ADA parking is available on a first-come, first-serve basis in designated lots. Mobility assistance is available in outer lots.

rolling_loud_los_angeles.note: No specific parking options or pricing details are provided for Rolling Loud Los Angeles at Hollywood Park. Visitors are encouraged to explore nearby parking facilities or consider alternative transportation methods.

summerfest.note: Patrons are encouraged to park in downtown Milwaukee parking structures and use Summerfest Shuttles for direct access to the festival. Shuttles run every 15 minutes from designated Park and Ride lots with a round-trip fare of $12 for adults and $6 for reduced fare riders.

pitchfork_music_festival.note: Parking options around the Pitchfork Music Festival venue may include street parking and nearby parking garages. It's advisable to arrive early to secure a spot, as parking can be limited during the event.

new_orleans_jazz_heritage_festival.note: Parking is available at the rear of the George and Joyce Wein Jazz & Heritage Center, where the entrance is also located. No pricing information is provided.

newport_folk_festival.note: On site parking is limited at Fort Adams State Park, and purchasing a parking pass in advance is strongly encouraged. On site parking sales are credit card only, and once full, attendees will be directed to an offsite satellite lot. Parking for patrons with disabilities is available with a designated lot and shuttle service.
newport_folk_festival.rideshare: Follow the signs for designated dropoff and pickup locations for ridesharing services.

newport_jazz_festival.note: On site parking at Fort Adams State Park is limited and requires advance purchase of a parking pass. On site parking sales are credit card only, and cash is not accepted. Once full, attendees will be directed to an offsite satellite lot.
newport_jazz_festival.rideshare: If you use a ridesharing service such as UBER or LYFT, please follow the signs for designated dropoff and pickup locations.

austin_city_limits_music_festival.note: There is no official parking garage affiliated with the venue, but nearby options are available. Limited valet parking is offered at the W Hotel for ACL Live ticketholders on a first-come, first-served basis. Metered parking starts at $2 per hour and varies by time and day.
austin_city_limits_music_festival.rideshare: Let Lyft be your ride to the action! Use code ACLLIVELYFT for 50% off your first 2 rides (up to $10/ride).

when_we_were_young.note: Self parking is complimentary for all guests and visitors at Circus Circus Las Vegas. Oversized vehicles can park in the RV area for an additional $20.00 per day, subject to availability.
when_we_were_young.rideshare: Uber and Lyft ride-share services are available, with pick-up and drop-off near the main entrance.

life_is_beautiful.note: Parking options at Life is Beautiful Grounds vary by event and location. Tailgating may be allowed before certain events but typically not during or after. Consider checking the weather to choose the best parking spot.

lightning_in_a_bottle.note: Parking passes are required for those driving to the event. Attendees can enter during regular gate hours, but no overnight parking or roadside camping is allowed.

music_midtown.note: The parking garage is centrally located in the park and shared with the Atlanta Botanical Garden. It is cashless, requiring payment by credit or debit card, and offers the first 30 minutes for free. The garage is accessible from the lowest floor.

iii_points.note: There is no onsite parking at Factory Town. Carpooling or using rideshare services is highly recommended. Be cautious of unauthorized parking operators near the venue.

hard_summer_music_festival.note: No specific parking options or pricing details are provided for the HARD Summer Music Festival. Visitors are encouraged to explore nearby parking facilities or consider alternative transportation methods.

moonrise_festival.note: The Moonrise Festival is permanently closed, and no specific parking options or pricing details are available. Visitors should check for nearby public parking or alternative transportation options.

country_thunder_wisconsin.note: Parking options and pricing details are not specified on the provided page. It is recommended to check the official website closer to the event for updates. Arrive early to secure a parking spot.

burning_man.note: Parking at Burning Man is typically limited to designated areas within Black Rock City. Attendees are advised to plan ahead and follow the event's guidelines for vehicle entry and parking. There are no traditional parking lots or garages, and parking is generally included with the purchase of a vehicle pass.

riot_fest.note: No specific parking options, pricing, or tips are mentioned on the provided page. Attendees are encouraged to check local parking facilities or use public transportation.

essence_festival_of_culture.note: Ample parking is available at the Convention Center for a daily fee, but overnight parking is prohibited. ADA parking is available, and specific needs can be addressed via email.
essence_festival_of_culture.rideshare: If arriving or departing by taxi or rideshare, use the designated Taxi/Rideshare Zone.

sxsw_music_film_interactive.note: Driving and parking in downtown Austin during SXSW can be expensive and time-consuming due to street closures and increased traffic. It is recommended to use alternative transportation options like walking, shuttles, or rideshares.

cma_fest.note: Festival organizers encourage the use of rideshare, SpotHero, or public parking options. Reserve parking in advance through SpotHero for convenience and affordability.

made_in_america.note: Parking is available at the National Constitution Center's parking garage, accessible from Race Street. Pricing details are not provided, so checking on arrival is recommended.

the_gorge_amphitheatre.note: General admission parking is included with your ticket. For easier entry and exit, consider upgrading to Reserved Parking, Star Parking, or Star Parking Plus. Arrive early to avoid heavy traffic and long wait times.
